```cpp
#include <stdio.h>
int main (){
    int c;
    scanf ("%d", &c);
    if (c >= 30 && c <= 40) {
        printf ("Yes");
    } else {
        printf ("No");
    }
    return 0;
}
```

Explanation: I replaced the conditional operator (`?:`) with an if-else statement to make the code more readable and easier to understand.